{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "top", "internal": "ropgeometry", "icon": "OBJ/geo", "since": "17.5", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["ROP Geometry Output"], "extent": [87, 111]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Creates work items that cook an embedded Geometry ROP node "], "extent": [111, 179]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node is a subnet that contains a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/top/ropfetch", "type": "link", "text": ["ROP Fetch"], "fullpath": "/nodes/top/ropfetch"}, " TOP node and\na ROP Network with a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/out/geometry", "type": "link", "text": ["Geometry"], "fullpath": "/nodes/out/geometry"}, " ROP node. The parameters on\nthe Geometry node are promoted onto this node\u2019s interface. Relevant parameters\nfrom the ROP Fetch are also available, including controls for using this node\nto cook work items for a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/dyno/distribute", "type": "link", "text": ["distributed sim"], "fullpath": "/dyno/distribute"}, "."], "extent": [179, 557]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The subnet also contains a SOP network as a dive target, which can be used with\nthe ROP Geometry. By default the built-in SOP network is disabled, and will\nonly be used when the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Use External SOP"]}, " toggle is turned off."], "extent": [557, 779]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [779, 784], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If the SOP network you are cooking with this node is threaded (such as most\n    simulations) you will be using most of the computer\u2019s CPU resources.  For \n    this reason you should ensure that only one such work item is cooking at a time."], "extent": [784, 1029]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/top/localscheduler", "type": "link", "text": ["Local Scheduler"], "fullpath": "/nodes/top/localscheduler"}, ", this means adding the \n    ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Single"]}, " job parm on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["ROP Geometry Output"]}, " node and toggling it ON."], "extent": [1029, 1188]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["For the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/top/hqueuescheduler", "type": "link", "text": ["HQueue Scheduler"], "fullpath": "/nodes/top/hqueuescheduler"}, ", this might mean adding\n    and setting the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["CPUs per Job"]}, " job parm."], "extent": [1188, 1316]}], "container": true}, {"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1316, 1321], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"type": "code", "text": ["$HH/help/files/pdg_examples/top_distributedsim"]}, " example shows how you can use this node to cook a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/dyno/distribute", "type": "link", "text": ["distributed simulation"], "fullpath": "/dyno/distribute"}, "."], "extent": [1321, 1473]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["The ", {"type": "code", "text": ["$HH/help/files/pdg_examples/top_rop"]}, " example shows how you can use this node to cache source and simulation geometry to disk."], "extent": [1473, 1611]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1611, 1620], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/top/ropfetch", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/top/ropfetch"}], "extent": [1620, 1642]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["ROP Geometry Output"], "summary": ["Creates work items that cook an embedded Geometry ROP node "]}